Sentencas: Redox behavior of a Ni-Y(2)O(3)(-)stabilized ZrO2 (YSZ) composite anode support and the performance degradation of an anode-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) were studied under complete oxidation and reduction conditions (degrees of oxidation and reduction = 100%).
Titulo: Redox-induced performance degradation of anode-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Materials characterization studies showed that the exposure time in oxidizing and reducing atmospheres played a critical role in the degradation of the porous structures and the physical properties of the anode support.
Titulo: Redox-induced performance degradation of anode-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In particular, the redox cycling with an 8 h exposure time resulted in the cracking of YSZ network, leading to significant decay of the mechanical strength.
Titulo: Redox-induced performance degradation of anode-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization experiments on the redox-cycled anode-supported tubular cell showed serious performance degradation as a result of the decreases of open-circuit potential and power density.
Titulo: Redox-induced performance degradation of anode-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The ac-impedance measurements combined with microstructural observations indicated that the performance degradation resulted mainly from (i) the degradation of anode support, (ii) microcracks across the whole cell, and (iii) interface delamination.
Titulo: Redox-induced performance degradation of anode-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells
